        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 11:04AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 1103 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mccoll, or near Laurinburg, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Maxton, Antioch, Wagram, Gibson, East Laurinburg, and
Laurel Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
